{{Unreferenced|date=July 2007}} {{Infobox music festival | name =Half Moon Party | image =Image:halfmoondeiz.jpg | caption =The Half Moon Party in [[Ko Pha Ngan]], [[Thailand]]. | location =[[Ko Pha Ngan]], [[Thailand]] | years_active = 2002-Present | founders = Jao Entertainement Group | dates =1 week before the Full Moon and 1 week after the Full Moon | genre = [[Electronic music]], etc. | attendance = 2000-4000 | capacity = | website = https://www.halfmoonfestival.com/ }} The '''Half Moon Festival'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.halfmoonfestival.com/|title=Half Moon Festival|accessdate=29 May 2017}}</ref> is an outdoor [[dance music]] ([[rave]]) event on the island of [[Ko Pha Ngan]], [[Thailand]] held on the [[Lunar phase#Phases of the moon|half moon]], one week before and one week after the [[full moon]]. The promoters mainly employ local [[Disc jockey|DJs]] using [[Compact Disc|CD]] decks rather than [[Gramophone record|vinyl]]. Various guest DJs play unannounced sets but the event does not book big name stars.
The Half Moon Festival complements the bigger [[Full Moon Party]] events. It is held in its own venue in a forest north of the Ban Tai village, between Thong Sala and Haad Rin.
==See also== *[[List of electronic music festivals]]
