===Unrecognised Reigns===
On 17 November 2018 at Capital Pro Wrestling's MitchellMania event, NZWPW owner Martin Stirling was seen taking the NZWPW Heavyweight Championship from the then current champion Bryant. Bryant was told by Stirling that he took it for "maintenance".

The following Tuesday NZWPW announced on its Facebook page that Bryant's as well as the previous champion, Wayne La Perfeccion's reigns are not official. The reason given by NZWPW was that title changes after "Dreamcatcher" Phil Woodgate left as CWO are no longer official. 

Therefore, the following 2 championship reigns were previously recognised, but are no longer recognised by the promotion as of 20 November 2018:
